    "The performance is defined as the expected cumulative reward over the initial state distribution 0:",
    "To optimize G from a given state s, we can utilize the state-value function V ∶ S → ℝ which estimates the desirability of being in a particular state s under policy:",
    "By updating the policy to maximize the state-value function, the agent iteratively optimizes the expected performance G. Similarly, we can employ the action-value function Q ∶ S × A → ℝ, also known as Q-function, which estimates the value of selecting a specific action a in a given state s under policy:",
    "In DRL, the policy or value functions are represented by neural networks.",
    "In an N multi-agent MG, in comparison to an MDP, we need to consider the involvement of multiple agents A, denoted as we discussed in Sect. 2.1."
